Job Title: Senior AI Engineer role / GenAI / LLM's / ML / Sydney / Permanent
Ad Text:
Senior AI Engineer role / GenAI / LLM's / ML / Sydney / Permanent

About the company
Our client is a leading Australian financial services organisation based in Sydney, they are investing in the AI and Data space, and looking to bring on a Senior AI engineer to join the team. 

About the role
This hands-on Senior AI Engineer role is centred on building scalable, production-ready AI solutions. Reporting into technology leadership, you’ll collaborate with software engineers, data teams and product stakeholders to embed AI into enterprise systems, set engineering standards, and mentor team members.

Benefits
Competitive remuneration package (flexible on experience)
Hybrid flexible work arrangements
Strong focus on professional growth and learning
Supportive, collaborative and innovative culture
Duties/Key responsibilities
Design, develop and deploy enterprise-grade AI/ML platforms and solutions
Architect scalable systems that integrate AI into core applications
Establish engineering standards, testing practices and MLOps frameworks
Collaborate cross-functionally to deliver reliable production systems
Stay current with emerging AI and software engineering tools and practices
Skills and experience
software engineering background with strong foundations in design patterns and testing
AI/ML engineering, including production deployment and lifecycle management
Experience with generative AI, LLMs or model fine-tuning on cloud platforms (AWS preferred)
Strong understanding of MLOps, CI/CD pipelines and automation
Ability to mentor engineers and lead technical best practice
Awareness of AI governance, bias and model integrity considerations
If you’re interested in this opportunity and feel you’re the right fit please click “apply” 

About Allura Partners
Allura Partners was founded to support private equity firms by placing C-Suites to lead, transform, and scale portfolio companies. Today, in addition to our proven private equity specialisation, we’ve become a trusted partner for major ASX-listed and private enterprises in Australia, offering executive search, recruitment, and business transformation. Known for integrity, reliability, and results, our expertise spans Executive Search, Accounting & Finance, Transformation & Change, and Technology & Digital. We connect businesses and top-tier talent, exceeding expectations and driving lasting impact.

Senior AI Engineer role / GenAI / LLM's / ML / Sydney / Permanent

Company Description


Lendi Group is a market-leading digital platform business focused on transforming the home loan industry. It operates the country’s #1 retail mortgage broker – the iconic Aussie Home Loans franchise – and the Australia’s #1 digital mortgage brand, Lendi.

Together, with its national network of 1,300 brokers and 230 retail stores, the Lendi Group brands give all Australians the power of choice, and confidence, in one of life’s biggest financial decisions.

Building on this market-leading foundation, Lendi Groups vision is to be the undisputed place for Australians to buy and own property through our new Aussie Homes propositions.

Lendi Group’s loan book is more than $100b and it was named Australia’s Aggregator of the Year for 2024

Diversity, Equality, and Inclusion are fundamental to the success of Lendi Group. We’re passionate about fostering an environment where our team members feel valued and supported and we celebrate everyone’s unique identity.

To learn more about life at Lendi Group check out our blog: https://www.lendi.com.au/inspire/category/life-at-lendi/

About the role?

As an RPA/AI Engineer, you will design, build, and deliver automation and AI initiatives that enable smarter, more efficient ways of working. You’ll collaborate with teams across the business, ensure adoption of new technologies, and adapt quickly to emerging tools and opportunities.

Job Description


Deliver AI Projects – Design, develop, and implement automation and AI initiatives, ensuring adoption and tangible business outcomes.
Drive Adoption that Sticks – Support teams with training, communication, and hands-on guidance to embed new ways of working.
Keep Projects Moving – Adapt quickly to changing priorities while ensuring projects remain on track and achieve outcomes.
Collaborate Widely – Partner with business units and stakeholders to identify opportunities, drive efficiencies, and accelerate adoption across the organisation.

Qualifications


Strong understanding of AI tools and their practical applications in business workflows.
Experience with AI engineering, including:
Building Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines.
Prompt engineering for effective AI/LLM use cases.
Working with LLM frameworks (e.g., LangChain, Semantic Kernel, or similar).
Exposure to agentic AI use cases (AI agents, task automation orchestration).
Hands-on experience with Power Automate and Copilot Studio, including solution design and deployment.
Willingness to work across a variety of AI and automation tools as needed.
Strong problem-solving skills and adaptability in a fast-paced environment.
Excellent collaboration and communication skills with the ability to influence and guide stakeholders.

What We’re Looking For

A proactive problem-solver who can balance technical expertise with business impact.
Someone ready to adapt to and learn new AI/automation tools as they emerge.
A collaborative team player who thrives in environments of change and innovation.

Additional Information


Lendi Group teams operate across Australia and the Philippines. We’re committed to creating a new era of seamless connection in property finance by changing the way Australians experience property lending, for good.

A few of the benefits that our people rave about include:

A vibrant, relaxed, yet professional culture
Holistic wellbeing programs offering 24/7 support, including medical, mental health, and financial wellbeing services to enable our workforce to thrive at home and work
Generous Paid Parental Leave: we celebrate our growing Lendi Group family with 18-26 weeks leave for primary carers and up to 4 weeks for secondary carers
An additional week’s Loyalty Leave each year after reaching 3 years of service
Wellness initiatives with a strong focus on psychological safety
Social groups such as our industry-leading Women in Technology group.

Our culture is guided by our 3 core values: We Are Stronger United; Act Like You Own It; and Keep Home Loans Human. Our values are part of our core DNA that helps Lendi Group to attract, engage and evolve the right talent and build best-in-class products.

Feeling like you don’t meet all the skills listed? That’s ok; we are always on the lookout for different skills, experience, and qualities and so we’d still like to hear from you.

#lendigroup #LI-GR2 #LI-hybrid

WHO ARE WE?



NetComm is a leading manufacturer of innovative broadband products for global service providers. For over 40 years NetComm has built an extensive access device portfolio including Fixed Wireless, Fibre Extension and Home Broadband Networking products designed to meet the growing needs of today's home, business and industrial applications. 

 

We are looking for a motivated Manufacturing Test Automation Engineer to lead the design, development and maintenance of our product manufacturing test systems.

 

 

WHAT WILL BE YOUR FOCUS?

·       Lead the design, development and maintenance of production test systems.

·       Collaborate cross-functionally with Hardware, Software and Project leads to define test strategies and to develop comprehensive manufacturing test requirements.

·       Develop RESTful APIs and Python libraries to interface with test equipment, devices under test (DUTs), and manufacturing execution system (MES).

·       Design and implement automated test scripts and applications using Python and/or C/C++ for functional and system-level testing.

·       Deploy and maintain automated test systems (ATS) across Contract Manufacturer/3PL ensuring proper training, quality, efficiency, and cost optimization.

·       Apply automation best practices such as containerization and utilizing AI tools to streamline development and deployment workflows efficiently.

·       Support enhancement and maintenance of proprietary full-stack web application for production data management, enabling efficient manufacturing and logistics operations.

 

WHAT DO WE LOOK FOR IN YOU?

 

Experience: Telecommunications and/or electronics manufacturing industry.

Technical Expertise: Python, MySQL, Docker, Git, REST APIs.

Technical Know-how: Familiarity with manufacturing test systems, hardware/software integrations, and AI-assisted development tools.

Software Knowledge: Strong understanding of software development principles, including software architecture, design patterns, and testing methodologies.

Ownership: Sense of responsibility to deliver and follow through.

Critical Thinking: Analytical and problem-solving skills.

Teamwork: Ability to thrive in fast-paced cross-functional teams.

 

 

WHAT'S IN IT FOR YOU? 
 

Inclusive and collaborative working environment.

Deep sense of work life balance.

Exposure to innovative technology.

Regular wellbeing and diversity focused initiatives.

Various perks including company sponsored insurance, recognition award and others to look forward to.



 

We believe in the value of a vibrant, diverse and inclusive workforce where our team members feel valued, respected and empowered to help innovate and create strong connections with our customers.

 

We embrace differences and we welcome applications from people of all backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities and other diversity groups.

Job Title: Talent Register: Data Engineering Professionals - Level 4 - EL2
Ad Text:
ASIS is Australia’s overseas secret intelligence collection agency. Its mission is to protect and promote Australia’s vital interests through the provision of intelligence services as directed by the Australian Government.

ASIS employs people in a wide range of roles, including technologists. These roles require dynamic team players who enjoy working with stakeholders, team members and individually on projects. ASIS is looking for people who will be able to meet tight deadlines and work to support ASIS priorities. Successful candidates will have excellent coordination and administration skills, excellent verbal and written communication skills; and, strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills. Relevant tertiary qualifications and demonstrable experience will be highly regarded.

ASIS values workplace diversity and is committed to providing a supportive, inclusive and respectful work environment. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People, women, people with disabilities, people that identify as LGBTIQ+ and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds. We offer a competitive salary packing, including 22 days annual leave, shutdown between Christmas and New Year’s Day, 15.4% employer superannuation contribution, access to flex time (up to Level 6 only) and generous paid maternity/paternity leave.

Positions for these roles are based in Canberra and/or Adelaide CBD. This role requires the successful applicant to obtain and maintain a security clearance. 

Data Engineering Professionals (Level 4—EL2)

Are you keen to design and develop world-class capabilities, turning data into knowledge and operational outcomes? Are you passionate about building solutions to allow data to tell its story? ASIS offers an opportunity to achieve these goals in an uncompromisingly unique environment. As a Data Professional in ASIS, you will have the chance to actively enable our operational teams to make the best use of ASIS’s unique data assets. ASIS leverages the wide world of open source software and supplements it with our own development to deliver the bespoke tools required for the ASIS mission. Among our core languages are Python, Scala, Java, C++, Rust and JavaScript. Our toolset includes Spring, PyTorch, Tensorflow, Apache Spark, Apache Accumulo, Apache Hadoop, Apache NiFi, Apache Solr, Ansible and Git. We leverage structured and unstructured data, including geospatial and multilingual data sets of varying quality. Ideal candidates will be extraordinarily innovative, self-motivated and keen to use these toolsets to craft new systems that are simply not found in any other organisation. If this sounds like an environment you could thrive in, then apply for one of these unique positions.

Application Levels

A Level 4 candidate would be expected to be new to the area and work under the guidance and supervision of a more senior officer.

A candidate at the Level 5 level would be expected to have one to two years real-world experience and will be working under some supervision.

A Level 6 level candidate would be expected to have more experience and operate with limited supervision within a core group of developers.

A candidate at the EL1 level is expected to have substantial experience, and some deep technical expertise. They operate entirely independently and have the capacity to fulfil leadership roles as required.

EL2 candidates fulfil principal engineer or section leadership roles. They are expected to have substantial experience and significant deep subject matter expertise in their field of specialisation.

Specialisations

We have a number of positions available including:

 Site Reliability Engineers at Level 5 to EL2;

 Software Engineers at Level 4 to EL1;

 Data Specialists at Level 4 to Level 6

Please refer to the Selection Documentation for the job available through our Careers Page for more information.

Job Title: Senior Engineering Manager, Data and AI
Ad Text:
Senior Engineering Manager, Data and AI

Own the build of modern data platforms and next‑gen AI that power millions of customer and merchant experiences
Lead a high performing, values led engineering squad that ships quality at pace and lifts Data and AI capability across Zip
Hybrid working from our Sydney office, with two team connect days per week
Write your story with a career at Zip


A role in Zip’s Data and AI squad will see you partner with teams across the business to supply fast, reliable and future ready data, and to design and deliver AI systems that power brilliant customer, merchant and Zipster experiences. You will help operationalise Data and AI across a range of processes and journeys, so we can solve big problems with clarity, speed and measurable outcomes.

As our Senior Engineering Manager, Data and AI, you will lead the design, delivery and optimisation of modern data platforms and AI services, and scale our engineering capability so that resilient, secure and sound solutions make a real impact. You will collaborate closely with product, analytics, risk and technology leaders to turn prototypes into production grade systems and champion responsible, customer first use of Data and AI.

What you’ll own

Set the engineering vision and roadmap for data platforms and AI services in partnership with leaders across Zip
Build, coach and empower a diverse team of data and AI engineers to do their best work and grow their careers
Uplift engineering practices across Data Engineering, MLOps and AI productisation to ensure quality, reliability and scalability
Deliver secure, observable and cost aware data pipelines and services that enable analytics and machine learning at scale, leveraging platforms like Databricks, Snowflake, DBT and AWS.
Partner with enterprise technology teams to integrate data and AI into customer and merchant facing applications
Embed responsible data and AI practices, governance and risk management in everything we build
Balance near term delivery with long term sustainability and innovation
What you’ll bring to the team


Zipsters work on a broad range of initiatives and our skills and experiences all look a little different. What really matters to us is that you are a great fit with our Values and have a desire to learn and grow. So whether you meet some or all of the attributes below, we would still love to hear from you.

Proven success leading high performing data or AI engineering teams, ideally in fintech, payments or high growth tech
Depth in data engineering and data infrastructure, with practical knowledge of modern cloud data stacks, ideally including Databricks, Snowflake, DBT and AWS
Hands on experience taking machine learning and Gen AI solutions to production, including MLOps and lifecycle management
Familiarity with advanced AI patterns such as retrieval augmented generation and multi agent approaches, and the pragmatism to use the right tool for the job
Strong stakeholder management, with the ability to influence and align senior partners around outcomes
A track record of building inclusive, ethical and customer centric systems that meet regulatory and trust standards
A mindset that embraces AI and new tools to adapt, learn and grow.
An aptitude for identifying and managing risks. Whether you are a People Manager or an Individual Contributor, we are all leaders at Zip, therefore effective risk management is important to how we run our business and part of all our roles.
Our values in your DNA. Customer First, Own It, Stronger Together and Change the Game.
What you’ll get in return


As we write this next exciting chapter in our story, we will continue to move at pace and embrace change. For you, this might mean opportunities to learn new skills with hands on experience, broader responsibilities, or the buzz of seeing your work impact customers faster.

Zip is a place where you will get out exactly what you put in. When you join the team, we will do our best to make sure you can be yourself and surround yourself with smart, friendly colleagues and leaders who have your back, so that you can make the big things happen.

Zipsters tell us these are just some of the best things about working here. You will also receive:

25 days paid leave annually, including birthday leave and quarterly wellbeing days
16 weeks paid parental leave for primary carers, and four weeks for supporting carers
Family support policies including miscarriage bereavement leave and domestic violence leave
Mental health and wellness initiatives, including a wellbeing allowance, free access for you and family members to our wellbeing platform Sonder, discounted private health insurance and great rates on fitness sessions through ClassPass
2 days paid volunteering leave, 2 days study leave and 2 days religious or cultural leave per year
Fee free Zip products and discounts with Zip merchant partners in Australia
Team social events, epic offices, free breakfast daily and weekly free lunches in Sydney and Melbourne
Access the Flare Benefits Hub and Novated Leasing to save on everyday expenses and potentially reduce the cost of car ownership
Be a part of a team that reflects the diversity of our customers


We pride ourselves on being a workplace that provides equal opportunities to people of all ages, cultural backgrounds, sexual orientations, gender identities, abilities, veteran status and everything else that makes you unique.

Equally, we are committed to ensuring our recruitment processes are accessible and inclusive. Please let us know if there are any adjustments that need to be made to ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.

And finally… get to know us


Zip Co Limited is a digital financial services company, offering innovative, people centred products across Australia and New Zealand and the United States. We are proud to be a values led business and our values Customer First, Own It, Stronger Together and Change the Game guide us in everything we do.

#LI-Hybrid

We are seeking an experienced Data Engineer to join a high-profile government program focused on transport safety and systems transformation. This role offers the chance to work on complex data integration projects, build scalable pipelines, and apply data governance standards that make a real impact. You’ll be part of a collaborative Agile team, working with modern cloud technologies and large-scale data systems.

Responsibilities:

Design and maintain data architectures, canonical models, and schema mappings to ensure system interoperability.
Build and optimise ETL/ELT pipelines for ingestion, transformation, validation, and publication of transport datasets.
Apply data quality and governance frameworks to ensure accuracy, consistency, and reliability.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams (developers, analysts, project managers) in an Agile environment.
Document pipelines, schemas, lineage, and quality processes to support maintainability and future improvements.
Experience:

Extensive experience in data modelling and canonical model design, including schema mappings.
Hands-on expertise with ETL/ELT pipelines in cloud environments (e.g., AWS, Snowflake, PostgreSQL, Liquibase).
Strong background in data validation, testing frameworks, and pipeline monitoring.
Demonstrated ability to optimise data processes for scalability, performance, and governance.
Experience working in an Agile delivery environment with strong collaboration and communication skills.

Hours:  8:30 - 5:00pm (AEST)
Days: Monday to Friday (38 hrs/week)

About the Company

Provider Choice is a trusted leader in supporting NDIS participants, their families, and service providers. Our team ensures participants receive the guidance and support they need to manage their NDIS plans effectively. With a focus on delivering high-quality service and maintaining compliance with NDIS guidelines, we play a vital role in helping participants achieve their goals.

About the Role

We’re seeking a Senior AI Engineer to lead the development of generative AI features and machine learning systems, with a focus on fraud detection and risk analysis. You’ll work across teams to build and deploy scalable AI solutions, optimise LLMs, and drive continuous innovation. As a senior team member, you’ll also mentor others and promote best practices.


Key Responsibilities:

Lead the development of generative AI features and machine learning systems, including fraud detection models.

Research, analyse and consult on system needs, limitations, risks, and opportunities for enhancements across processes, tools and applications.

Work cross-functionally to build and deploy scalable, intelligent solutions.

Build and optimise generative AI models (e.g., LLMs).

Develop ML systems for fraud detection and risk analysis.

Implement and manage technical security controls, conduct forensic analysis, manage encryption/decryption, and mitigate risks across the product lifecycle.

Collaborate with product and engineering teams to integrate AI solutions.

Collect and analyse metrics, develop strategies for efficiency, cost-effectiveness, and ongoing delivery of high-performing, secure software solutions.

Ensure continuous innovation.

Mentor team members and promote ML best practices.




What’s on Offer

Reimbursable NDIS Worker Check.

Strong emphasis on work-life balance, allowing flexible working arrangements.

A workplace that invests in its people and celebrates achievements.

Work alongside a team of tech pioneers to be at the forefront of NDIS AI innovation.




What We’re Looking For:

7+ years’ professional experience delivering generative AI solutions.

Previous NDIS experience highly desirable but not required.

Comfortable using modern AI-powered development tools (e.g., Azure, Langchain, OpenAI, Gemini, etc).

Degree in relevant area such as software development, computer science or similar.




Why Join Us:

At Provider Choice, you’ll be part of a team that values professional growth, collaboration, and making a meaningful impact in the lives of NDIS participants.

If this opportunity resonates with you, submit your CV today – we can’t wait to hear from you!

About Adactin

Adactin Group is a 100% Australian-owned global IT consulting company, headquartered in Sydney. We are a trusted technology partner helping organisations drive end-to-end digital transformation through our deep expertise in Microsoft and AWS ecosystems, AI-powered Digital Engineering, and future-ready Quality Assurance.

Our managed delivery approach, backed by domain expertise, ensures successful outcomes for every project.

At Adactin, we believe in the power of our people. We foster a dynamic and supportive environment where your career can grow alongside exciting projects that shape the future of technology. Join us, and be part of a team committed to innovation, excellence, and making a difference.

Seeking for Senior Data Engineers for a well know Insurance client
based in Sydney only

The Senior Data Engineer is responsible for the design, development, and optimisation of data pipelines, transformations, and platform

components within cloud-based data ecosystem. This role combines hands-on delivery with technical leadership across projects,

enabling scalable and reusable data assets that support analytics, insights, and operational use cases.

As a senior member of the Data Platform Engineering team, the role contributes to the standardisation of engineering practices,

mentors junior engineers, and proactively collaborates with Solution Designers, DevOps, and Data Ops to ensure quality, performance,

and operational readiness.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:

· Develop and maintain reliable, performant, and reusable data pipelines using AWS (e.g. Glue, Lambda) and Snowflake

· Translate solution designs and modelling specifications into technical implementation with minimal supervision

· Contribute to design discussions and code reviews, helping uplift engineering quality and consistency

· Embed logging, error handling, and observability features into all pipeline work

· Apply CI/CD practices and collaborate with DevOps to automate build, test, and deployment processes

· Support solution scalability by building with reusability and modularisation in mind

· Mentor junior Data Engineers, contributing to technical documentation and team knowledge sharing

· Collaborate with Data Engineers, contributing to technical documentation and team knowledge sharing

· Collaborate with Data Ops on tuning, deployment readiness, and continuous improvement actions

Overview 

The Senior AI Technical Consultant is a pivotal role within the AI4 Group's dedicated advisory businesses, CopilotHQ and Navigator AI Advisory. This individual serves as the organisation's primary AI Technical Subject Matter Expert (SME), responsible for providing deep technical guidance and architectural leadership to both clients and internal delivery teams. The Consultant will excel at translating complex business challenges and infrastructure constraints into coherent, viable, and secure AI-driven solutions. 

We are looking for someone who is energised and thrives in a fast-paced, fast-evolving, scaling AI-first business and can bring that drive to our advisory practice. 

 

Key Responsibilities 

1. Technical Advisory and Executive Engagement 

Peer-to-Peer Consulting: Engage with client CTOs, Heads of Technology, and AI Leads at a peer level, articulating complex AI concepts and architectural decisions clearly and confidently. 

Strategy Translation: Synthesise complex business requirements, organisational infrastructure, and operational constraints into detailed technical specifications for AI models and solution architectures. 

Technical Feasibility: Lead and manage the technical feasibility assessment for proposed AI initiatives, ensuring solutions are robust, scalable, and practical within the client's existing technology landscape. 

2. Architecture and Innovation Leadership 

Technical Authority: Act as the internal authority on the rapidly evolving AI landscape, including staying current with the latest AI technical releases, model advancements, development protocols, and security best practices. 

Architectural Design: Design and recommend optimal AI architecture, development stacks, and integration strategies for custom and off-the-shelf AI/ML solutions (including Generative AI, MLOps, and Data Pipelines). 

Standards & Governance: Define and enforce technical standards and quality protocols for AI solution development across all projects. 

3. Delivery Guidance and Team Enablement 

Technical Leadership: Partner with internal (onshore and offshore) development teams, providing technical oversight, direction, and hands-on guidance during the solution development and integration phases. 

Deployment Management: Facilitate the seamless development, testing, and deployment of integrated AI solutions within both the AI4 group’s and client environments. 

Mentorship: Mentor mid-level and junior technical staff on best practices in AI development and modern cloud architecture. 

 

Qualifications and Experience 

Experience: Minimum of 7+ years of professional experience in software engineering, technical consulting, or solutions architecture, with at least 3 years focused specifically on modern AI/ML development and deployment. 

Domain Expertise: Deep technical knowledge of cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP) as they relate to AI services, data warehousing, and infrastructure design. 

Communication: Exceptional ability to communicate highly technical topics to non-technical stakeholders and executive audiences. 

Technical Depth: Demonstrated expertise in AI models, including proficiency in at least one major language (e.g., Python) and relevant AI/ML frameworks. 

A "Nice to Have": Demonstrated ability to hands-on develop prototypes or production-ready code.

About Us 

Future Secure AI (FSAI) is a leading enterprise AI company that was created in deep partnership with one of the world's largest financial institutions.

Operating as an enterprise company with deep relationships at C-suite with large global enterprises, FSAI believes humans and AI Workers will collaborate seamlessly to raise organisational performance. FSAI has dozens of partnerships with leading companies in most industries and regions globally.

FSAI has a strategic focus on expanding globally as we continue our extraordinary journey to transform the world with the most cutting-edge artificial intelligence.

The Opportunity

We are hiring Intermediate Software Engineers to help us build the product and platform. You will collaborate with client and partner technical teams, alongside our internal members to enhance tech solutions. 

This role requires you to efficiently navigate between detailed coding and broader business and product strategies. You must be highly organised, adept in cross-functional teams, and passionate about advancing AI technology.

Key responsibilities

Enable enterprise customers to deploy a diverse and dynamic range of AI agents from multiple third-party platforms (including models, LLMs, micro-services and even orchestration layers) through their own secure and scalable platform.

Develop innovative AI products for reputable global clients, focusing on Node.js, and integrating AI with use of LangChain, LangGraph, Flowise

Discover and incorporate new partnerships, products, and technologies, including cutting-edge LLMs and AI models, from both established and emerging vendors.

Design and implement algorithms specifically for AI agents, utilizing your Node.js expertise and understanding of AI frameworks.

Strategise on the seamless integration of new features and APIs across various platforms in large-scale enterprise environments, leveraging your Node.js and potential Python skills.

Exhibit a deep commitment to understanding user needs and meticulous attention to detail, ensuring our solutions not only meet but exceed user expectations.

Uphold and exceed enterprise-grade compliance standards, such as SOC2, ensuring our products are secure and reliable.

Requirements

Not only do you have impressive problem-solving skills, we also value your leadership mindset and ability to proactively take charge in a fast moving environment.

You’ve worked in environments where integrations were messy: a patchwork of vendors, products, and point-to-point connections that no one really owned. You knew it wasn’t sustainable, but you weren’t given the mandate to fix it.

This role gives you that mandate.

Here, you’ll take responsibility for keeping critical integrations stable and reliable, while also leading the journey to a simplified, modern integration platform. You’ll inherit an environment with MuleSoft and AWS at its core, where APIs are already front-and-centre. But you’ll also help shape the next chapter: streamlining from 10+ vendors down to a best-of-breed iPaaS (Workato).

This is more than just operational support. You’ll be empowered to set standards, close gaps, reduce technical debt, and design integrations that make the business more agile. You’ll work with IT leaders who want someone decisive, someone who can own problems, figure things out quickly, and deliver outcomes.

What you’ll do

Design, build, and support integrations across enterprise apps using MuleSoft and AWS, ensuring they’re secure, scalable, and reliable.
Lead API management - from development to monitoring, gateways, and security - so data can flow seamlessly across ERP, CRM, HR and other core systems.
Tackle the current fragmentation challenge: stabilise legacy integrations while rationalising the vendor landscape, driving toward a Workato-led iPaaS future.
Deliver operational excellence: incident triage, root-cause analysis, runbooks, knowledge bases, continuous improvement.
Collaborate across IT and vendors to ensure changes, releases, and upgrades are governed, well-documented, and deliver value without disruption.

What you’ll bring

Strong hands-on experience with integration, plus proven capability in API development and management.
The ability to work with ambiguity: figuring things out when documentation is light, asking the right questions, and owning outcomes end-to-end.
Knowledge of modern integration patterns, monitoring/alerting, and operational support in complex enterprise environments.
Familiarity with ITIL/ITSM (ServiceNow/Jira), CI/CD, and good practice for governance and releases.
Bonus if you’ve worked with iPaaS platforms like Workato or Boomi, or if you’ve built reusable integration connectors and patterns.

Why this role

You’ll have impact: reducing complexity, setting integration standards, and driving toward a future-proof iPaaS.
You’ll have autonomy: a chance to “own it” from day one, solving problems and shaping the roadmap.
You’ll grow: working with modern tools, influencing the future-state architecture, and being trusted as the integration SME.

Next steps

If your CV isn’t up to date, no problem. Send what you have, or reach out to Matthew Downey at xceltium on matt@xceltium.com, or message on LinkedIn for a confidential chat. Every applicant will receive a response.

Job Description

Hey, hello, hiya, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work. That means if you want to do your thing in the office (if you're near one), at home or a bit of both, it's up to you.

What you’d be doing in this role

As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.

At the moment, this role is focused on:

Architect and code production‑ready automation services in Python/TypeScript, leveraging LangChain, LangGraph, and Canva’s internal platforms.

Take small prototypes and transform them into high quality production systems capable of being secure and resilient to the potentially thousands of people using them.

Fine‑tune, evaluate, and integrate LLMs, embeddings, and vector stores; where necessary own the full model lifecycle from experiment to rollout.

Instrument services with metrics, tracing, and alerting; own incident response and continuous improvement.

Collaborate with PMs, designers, and analysts to translate ambiguous business problems into measurable, AI‑powered solutions.

You're probably a match if

You have shipped AI or automation solutions that materially reduce manual effort and streamline processes.

You bring strong system-integration and troubleshooting skills across complex tech environments.

You communicate technical concepts clearly to engineers, Product Managers, designers, and leadership teams.

You take ownership, work autonomously, and flourish in a high-trust, collaborative culture.

You understand security, compliance, and governance requirements in enterprise settings.security, compliance, and governance requ

You stay curious - always learning, experimenting, and finding smarter ways to solve problems.

You possess a solid software development background and enjoy building at the edge of what’s possible.


About the team

This role will be embedded within the Content & Discovery supergroup, which sits at the heart of connecting our users with the right content at the right time. Our mission is to make Canva’s vast library of templates, elements, and media easily searchable, discoverable, and personalized, so every user finds inspiration and can create faster.


AI is one of Canva’s biggest goals. We’ve already shipped world‑class capabilities, from in‑house models to intelligent tools used by millions, but the biggest unlock is still ahead. Many of our internal workflows remain manual, decisions are slower than they should be, and data is often under‑used.

As a Senior AI Automation Engineer you’ll embed with teams across Canva to turn their manual processes into machine‑powered, always‑on systems. You’ll prototype in days, iterate quickly, and prove value before others finish writing the brief. Your work will help thousands of Canvanauts move faster and unlock 10× outcomes at scale.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too

Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers

An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more

Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We see AI as a powerful amplifier of creativity and technology at Canva.We’re evolving how we assess AI skills in our Technology hiring experience - you’ll tackle interactive, real-time challenges that reflect the kind of work we do. In some interviews, you may also be asked to solve a problem using an AI tool to show how you approach challenges with tech by your side. Your recruitment partner will walk you through what to expect.
We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.
